physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Best-corrected visual acuity was 20/30 in both eyes. Wide-spread reticular pseudodrusen (RPD) throughout the macula and above the arcades in both retinae.
Best-corrected visual acuity was 20/80 in the right eye and 20/20 in the left eye. Scattered intermediate drusen (63-125 mm) in both eyes in the mid periphery. No clinical or imaging evidence of RPD.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Best-corrected visual acuity and structural findings changed after the exenteration of the right eye.
